ğŸ§© Now, when it comes to arrays or objects

Hereâ€™s the key idea:

> const prevents reassignment of the variable, but does not make the contents (array or object) immutable.



That means the reference to the array cannot change, but the data inside it can still change.

Letâ€™s see examples:


